parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the camshaft position sensor can cause the engine warning light to illuminate, leading to engine stalling, reduced engine performance, and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The check engine warning light illuminates
the engine stalls
the vehicle shakes
the engine warning light remains on
the vehicle fails inspection
the engine catches fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Difficulty with Recall Repairs and Reimbursement
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the manufacturer to honor recall repairs and reimburse owners for out-of-pocket expenses can lead to frustration, financial burden, and potential safety risks if the defective component is not replaced.
symptoms: Difficulty in finding a repair shop
refusal of dealerships to honor the recall
lack of response from the manufacturer
out-of-pocket expenses for repairs
inability to get reimbursement.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake system failure can lead to extended stopping distances, increased risk of accidents, and potential fires.
symptoms: Brake pedal descends to the floor
soft brake pedal
excessive brake wear
premature wear of brake pads
squealing noise when applying brakes
ABS system works intermittently
brake pedal goes to the floorboard
extended stopping distances.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the camshaft position sensor can cause the check engine light to illuminate, engine noise, and engine stalling, leading to potential accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Check engine light illuminates
engine noise
engine dies
difficulty getting the recalled camshaft position sensor replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission problems can cause high RPM, difficulty shifting gears, and potential accidents.
symptoms: Transmission will not shift for 10-15 minutes
resulting in high RPM during that time frame.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Exhaust fumes entering the car interior can cause health risks and discomfort to occupants.
symptoms: Exhaust fumes enter the car interior
requiring windows to be rolled down to provide a non-lethal oxygen supply.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Difficulty in getting recalled parts replaced or dealers not being available to perform repairs can lead to frustration and potential safety risks.
symptoms: Difficulty in getting recalled parts replaced
dealers not being available to perform repairs
dealers not finding problems despite complaints.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash can increase the risk of injury or fatality to the vehicle occupants.
symptoms: Airbags fail to deploy in a crash
despite meeting the deployment threshold
resulting in potential injuries or fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Inability to Honor Recall Due to Dealer Closure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inability to honor a recall due to a dealer closure can leave vehicles with safety defects unrepaired, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Consumers are unable to find an authorized dealer to repair their vehicle due to dealer closure
despite having a recall notice.
